	<h1 class="w3-border-light-grey w3-padding-16">references</h1>
		<a href="doc/HIT-BIB.pdf" class="w3-bar-item w3-button w3-white" target="_blank">Lecturers' references</a>
		<p class="w3-opacity">selection out of the lecturers’ references, enriched by Florian Fischer and project members.</p>
	<br>
	<h2>general</h2>
		<p class="w3-opacity">general introductions, encyclopedias, literature, writing, history, miscellaneous</p>
		<p style="line-height: 1.8">
			<br>Fortson, Benjamin W. 2010. <i>Indo-European Language and Culture: an Introduction</i> (2nd ed.). 170–201. Chichester: Blackwell Wiley.
			<br>Haas, Volker. 2006. <i>Die hethitische Literatur: Texte, Stilistik, Motive</i>. Berlin, New York: Mouton de Gruyter.
			<br>Klein, Jared & Joseph, Brian D. (eds.). 2017.  <i>Handbook of Comparative and Historical Indo-European Linguistics</i>. Berlin, New York: Mouton de Gruyter.
			<br>Melchert, Craig H. 2017. Anatolian. In Mate Kapović (ed.), <i>The Indo-European Languages</i> (2nd ed.). 171-204. London, New York: Routledge.
			<br>Rüster, Christel & Neu, Erich. 1989. <i>Hethitisches Zeichenlexikon</i>. Wiesbaden: Harrassowitz.
			<br>Lexicity. 2016. <a href="http://lexicity.com/language/hittite/" style="color:#0000FF;" target="_blank"><i>Hittite</i>.</a> (Accessed 2021-07-06.)
			<br>Nègre, Xavier. 2002-2021. <a href="https://www.lexilogos.com/english/hittite_dictionary.htm" style="color:#0000FF;" target="_blank">Lexilogos</a>. (Accessed 2021-07-06.)
		</p><br>
	<h2>grammar</h2>
		<p class="w3-opacity">grammars, treatments of major grammatical domains</p>
		<p style="line-height: 1.8">
